TY  - JOUR
T1  - Asset Markets With Heterogeneous Information
AU  - Kurlat, Pablo
Y1  - 2016/01/01
PY  - 2016
DA  - 2016/01/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA12099
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
JA  - Econometrica
SP  - 33
EP  - 85
VL  - 84
IS  - 1
KW  - Asymmetric information
KW  - competitive equilibrium
KW  - fire sales
KW  - expertise
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA12099
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - This paper studies competitive equilibria of economies where assets are heterogeneous and traders have heterogeneous information about them. Markets are defined by a price and a procedure for clearing trades, and any asset can, in principle, be traded in any market. Buyers can use their information to impose acceptance rules which specify which assets they are willing to trade in each market. The set of markets where trade takes place is derived endogenously. The model can be applied to find conditions under which these economies feature fire sales, contagion, and flights to quality.
ER  - 

