TY  - JOUR
T1  - Equilibrium Labor Turnover, Firm Growth, and Unemployment
AU  - Coles, Melvyn G.
AU  - Mortensen, Dale T.
Y1  - 2016/01/01
PY  - 2016
DA  - 2016/01/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA10700
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
JA  - Econometrica
SP  - 347
EP  - 363
VL  - 84
IS  - 1
KW  - Labor turnover
KW  - stochastic equilibrium
KW  - unemployment
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA10700
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - This paper considers equilibrium quit turnover in a frictional labor market with costly hiring by firms, where large firms employ many workers and face both aggregate and firm specific productivity shocks. There is exogenous firm turnover as new (small) startups enter the market over time, while some existing firms fail and exit. Individual firm growth rates are disperse and evolve stochastically. The paper highlights how dynamic monopsony, where firms trade off lower wages against higher (endogenous) employee quit rates, yields excessive job-to-job quits. Such quits directly crowd out the reemployment prospects of the unemployed. With finite firm productivity states, stochastic equilibrium is fully tractable and can be computed using standard numerical techniques.
ER  - 

